<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9715> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9715" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 548" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7156> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7156" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 198. Quaestor. In Livy 32.7.9, he is described as a candidate for the consulship ex quaestura, but there is no record of the date (see MRR 1.329, note 2). Badian would place it after his military tribunate under the consul Marcellus in 208 (MRR 1.293) and before he was placed in command at Tarentum in 205 with imperium pro praetore (1.308). See Badian, JRS 61, 1961, 109, probably in 206. Proconsul, Greece and Macedonia, 197194. In MRR 1.336-337, refer to the gold coinage in Greece, Crawford, RRC 1.544, no. 548, 196 B.C. He was also honored by Phanoteus of Phocis (G. Klaffenbach, Chiron 1, 1971, 167-168; AEpig. 1972, 571).[179x]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2384> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2384" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Polyb. 23.4.1-15; cf. Liv. 39.48.2-4" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2377> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2377" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Prusias of Bithynia to protest against his war with Eumenes of Pergamum, and against Hannibal receiving refuge there (Polyb. 23.5.1; Liv. 39.51.1-12; Nep. Hann. 12; Plut. Flam. 20-21; App. Syr. 11; Dio fr. 64; Iustin. 32.4.8-12; Auct. Vir. Ill. 51.5; Eutrop. 4.5; Zon. 9.21; cf. Polyb. 23.13; Diod. 29.19; Val. Max. 9.2, ext. 2; Plin. NH 5.148; Oros. 4.20.29; Menipp. fr. 407, Bücheler). He was also active in the Peloponnese (Polyb. 23.5; cf. Plut. Flam. 17.3). See Lübker no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2376> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2376" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Polybius (23.5.1) says that Flamininus was sent \"to Prusias and Seleucus,\" but there is no record of his activity in Syria. On the date, see Nep. Hann. 12-13; cf. Hoffman, Hermes 73 (1938) 244-248; and esp. De Sanctis 4.1.243." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2236> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2236" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Sen. 42; Liv. 37.57.9-58.2, 41.9.9, and 13.4; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 454f.; Plut. Flam. 18.1. They reviewed the lists of senators and the knights, leased contracts, appointed Scipio Africanus for the third time Princeps Senatus, and completed the lustrum in 188 (Liv. 38.28.2, and 36.5-10; Plut. Flam. 18.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2186> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2186" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 192, Legates, no. b. He was active in Achaes, and intervened with Glabrio in Aetolia (Liv. 36.31-35; Plut. Flam. 15-17; Philop. 17.4). See Lübker no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2163> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2163" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to oppose Aetolian influence and rally the Greek communities against Antiochus (Liv. 35.23.5-8; note esp. Flamininus at Demetrias, 35.31, in Aetolia, 35.32-33, in Corinth, 35.34.1, and 39.1, and at the Achaean assembly, 35.48-50; and Villius' trip to Demetrias, 35.39; cf. Diod. 29.1; Plut. Flam. 15-17; Zon. 9.19). See also 191, Legates; and on Villius, Lübker, no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2103> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2103" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Greece and Macedonia (see 197-195). Completed his organization of Greece (cf. SIG\n     593), and returned with his army to celebrate a triumph over Macedonia and King Philip (Cic. Mur. 31; Pis. 61; Liv. 34.48-52; Act. Tr. Cap. and Tol., Degrassi 78f., 338f., 553; Val. Max. 5.2.6; Plut. Flam. 14; Eutrop. 4.2; cf. Grueber, CRRBM 1.154 f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 [1942] 179-181). See Lübker no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2081> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2081" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Greece and Macedonia (Liv. 33.43.6, imperium prorogued for a year). He joined the Achaeans in the war on Nabis of Sparta, and continued his organization of Greece (SIG\n     592; Liv. 34.22-41; Plut. Flam. 13.1-3; Iustin. 31.3.1; Eutrop. 4.2; Auct. Vir. Ill. 51; Oros. 4.20.2; Zon. 9.18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2042> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2042" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued as Proconsul in Greece and Macedonia (Liv. 33.25.11; see 197, Promagistrates). With the ten Legates, he made a treaty of peace with Philip, continued his arrangements for peace in Greece, and made the famous declaration of Greek freedom at the Isthmian games in{337} Corinth (Polyb. 18.43-47; Liv. 33.27-35; Plut. Flam. 9-12; Sull. 12.6; App. Mac. 9.1-4; cf. Val. Max. 4.8.5; Flor. 1.23.12-15; Eutrop. 4.2; Jerome Chr. p. 136 Helm; Oros. 4.20.1-2; Zon. 9.16). See Lübker no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2020> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2020" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Macedonia, with imperium prorogued until the Senate should send a successor (Polyb. 18.11.2, and 12.1; Liv. 32.28.9; Plut. Flam. 7.1-2). On his victory at Cynocephalae, and diplomatic activity in Greece, see Polyb. 18.18-27, 33-34, and 36-39; Liv. 33.1-15, 24.3-7, and 27-29; Plut. Flam. 7-9; App. Mac. 8, and 9.1-2; Flor. 1.23.11-12; Eutrop. 4.2; Oros. 4.20.5-6; cf. Iustin. 30.4.8-16. See Lübker, no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1985> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1985" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 32.7.12, and 8.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 452f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 9.16; on Paetus, Liv. 32.27.5; Dig. 1.2.2.38; and on Flamininus, Cic. Phil. 5.48; Polyb. 18.46.5; Oros. 4.20.1; and inscriptions, most of them to be dated after his consulship, ILS 8766- SIG\n     592; SIG(3) 593; 591, line 65; 674, line 51; and offerings at Delos, I. de Délos, 439a, 77; 442b, 85f.; 1429a, 21f.; 1441a, 105f.; 1446,15. Flamininus was assigned Macedonia (Liv. 32.8.4), successfully carried the war into Greece, and attempted to win the Achaean league to the Roman side (Liv. 32.9-15, and 17.4-24; Diod. 28.11; Frontin. Str. 2.13.8; Plut. Flam. 3-5; App. Mac. 5-7; Pausan. 7.8.2-3; Flor. 1.7.11; Auct. Vir. Ill. 51.1). His successes led to a parley with Philip at Nicaea, a truce, and the despatch of embassies\n     \n      1\n     \n     to Rome (Polyb. 18.1-10; Liv. 32.32-36; Plut. Flam. 5-7; App. Mac. 8; Iustin. 30.3.8-10; Zon. 9.16). On Flamininus, see Lübker, no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1968> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1968" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ex quaestura in this passage may indicate that Flamininus was Quaestor in 199 and proceeded immediately to the consulship; cf. ex aedilitate in Liv. 31.4.7, though the more usual expression for \"when aedile\" is qui tum aedilis erat, cf. Liv. 23.24.3; 24.9.4, and 43.6; 29.38.5; 32.7.13, and 27.7. Such phrases, however, can be used when some time elapses between the two offices: cf. Liv. 27.6.17, on Licinius Crassus, who was almost certainly Curule Aedile in 212, and in 210 ex aedilitate gradum ad censuram fecit; and Cic. Phil. 11.11, on Julius Caesar Strabo, who ex aedilitate (90 B.C.) consulatum petit in 88 B.C. Accordingly, Flamininus may have been Quaestor between 203, when he ceased to be in command pro praetore at Tarentum, and 199. He is listed here under the latest possible date." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1967> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1967" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected to the consulship for 198 ex quaestura\n     (Liv. 32.7.8-12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1955> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1955" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to supplement the colony of Venusia (Liv. 31.49.6; cf. Plut. Flam. 1.4, Narnia and Cosa). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1954> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1954" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plutarch confuses this commission with that for Narnia (see 199) and Cosa (refused in 199, Livy 32.2.7, but granted in 197-6, 33.24.8-9); and names Flaminius as its head (Flam. 1.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1953> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1953" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 31.49.5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1923> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1923" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected through the Pr. Urbanus to assign land in Samnium and Apulia to veterans who had served under Scipio in Africa (Liv. 31.4.1-3, and 49.5). On Villius, see Lübker, no. 1, on Quinctius, no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1822> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1822" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued as Propraetor at Tarentum (Liv. 29.13.6; Plut. Flam. 1). See Lübker, no. 11." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1779> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1779" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In command at Tarentum pro praetore (Liv. 29.13.6; cf. Plut. Flam. 1). See Lübker, no. 11, and Jashemski 35." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1698> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1698" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under the Consul Marcellus (Plut. Flam. 1; see Münzer, APF 117)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10205> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10205" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Macedonia et rege Philippo. MRR I.344, Itgenshorst no. 173, Rich no. 172." .
